1.    run Ramdisk by typing ./run.sh
2.    Operations in Ramdisk:
    (1)    creat pathname (e.g. creat haha)
        create a regular file under specified path (e.g. create haha.txt under root)
    (2) mkdir pathname (e.g. mkdir xixi)
        create a directory file under specified path (e.g. create xixi under root)
    (3)    ls
        show all the file under the current directory
    (4)    pwd
        show current directory
    (5)    cd pathname (e.g. cd xixi)
        go into specifed directory file (e.g. go into xixi)
    (6) cd ../pathname
        go back parent directory and then go into a new directory
    (7) rm pathname
        remove a file(regurlar/directory)
    // these are self-explanatory
    (8)    close pathname
    (9) open pathname

    // write and read from the file write/read position(default from beginning) 
    (10) write 
    (11) read
    (12) readdir 
        read the content of a directory file
    (13) lseek 
        change write/read position of a file opened by a process
    (14) test
        test bigfile (which we failed before)
